.TH "stack_trace_save_tsk_reliable" 9 "stack_trace_save_tsk_reliable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
stack_trace_save_tsk_reliable \- Save task stack with verification
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" stack_trace_save_tsk_reliable
.BI "(struct task_struct *tsk "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *store "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tsk" 12
Pointer to the task to examine
.IP "store" 12
Pointer to storage array
.IP "size" 12
Size of the storage array
.SH "RETURN"
An error if it detects any unreliable features of the
stack. Otherwise it guarantees that the stack trace is
reliable and returns the number of entries stored.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the task is not 'current', the caller *must* ensure the task is inactive.
